e for me so I don't forget some of the ideas I've gotten lately:<br>
<br>
1. &quot;Starving for Attention&quot; <br>
Mom pushes daughter into teen modelling. Constantly berating her about her weight. Daughter eventually dies of malnuitrition and comes back from the dead to haunt and starve mother.<br>
<br>
2. &quot;They're Real&quot;<br>
Father checks in on young daughter to find out why she can't sleep. Daughter explains there's a bogeyman in her closet. To show her that there isn't, father opens closet door. Bogeyman attacks father, but father manages to kill bogeyman. After calming down, father and daughter wonder what to do about this bogeyman corpse.<br>
<br>
3. &quot;Snuff&quot;<br>
University student purchases used digital camera online. When it arrives, the tape is still inside. Tape contain scene of a man torturing and then killing a young lady. The student later learns that the young lady in question was a senator's granddaughter and no one knows the identity of the killer, or that the entire event was recorded...<br>
<br>
4. &quot;Wishing Well&quot;<br>
An American collector travels to the Yorkshire countryside searching for forgotten collectibles. While visiting a farm house, the man learns from the owner that there is an old, dried up water well on his family's property that people have used as a wishing well for centuries. &quot;Throw in a penny and make a wish.&quot;<br>
<br>
Rationalising that there may be hundreds of old coins at the bottom of this well, the man returns later that night prepared for a descent into the well. At the bottom, the man doesn't find coins, but rather what lives there, a Well Troll who has the power to grant some wishes... <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=otakulad>OtakuLad</A> at: 8/19/03 8:15 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scoobeedo>Scoobeedo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/16/03 1:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm40.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=67.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Comic Horror Antholgy Ideas</span><hr size=1> Do you want to write this ideas down? Or make a comic? <br>
