&quot;Starving for Attention&quot; would be real-time.<br>
The mother is living through her daughter vicariously, in that she dreamed of being a model when she was younger, but became pregnant instead. Her daughter is attractive and successful, but her mother keeps pushing her into more and more work and to become thinner and thinner.<br>
<br>
The daughter, exhausted and over-worked, knows something is wrong but doesn't get a chance to seek help until it's too late... <br>
<br>
